s, $L_{\\rm bol}/M_{\\rm clump}$, indicate that\nthe HII regions are related to the most massive and luminous clumps. By\nestimating the production rate of ionizing photons, $Q$, from the submm-RRL\nflux, we find that the $Q$(H28$\\alpha$) measurements provide estimates of the\nLyman continuum photon flux consistent with those determined from 5 GHz radio\ncontinuum emission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Apr 2018 05:25:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-29"}
